HEADWORD: Drabbler
<hw>Drab"bler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
piece of canvas fastened by lacing to the bonnet of a sail, to give it a
greater depth, or more drop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

